1
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,780
[Episode 26]

2
00:01:37,260 --> 00:01:39,720
- Disgusting.
- Food's ready.

3
00:01:41,959 --> 00:01:43,600
Food's ready!

4
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,320
- Coming!
- Let's go, Yi.

5
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:49,940
You put on the most serious face of your life
for your wedding photos, Bo.

6
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:53,850
Don't look at my photos. That's not me.

7
00:01:53,850 --> 00:01:54,940
Is the soup ready?

8
00:01:54,940 --> 00:01:57,000
Coming, coming! Here it is.
Quick! It's hot! Watch out!

9
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,099
- Be careful.
- Don't touch.

10
00:01:59,099 --> 00:02:00,260
Are you two just going to drink?

11
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:03,480
- It's burning me!
- Knock it off.

12
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:06,360
- Qiao, beat him then.
- You really need a beating.

13
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,760
Don't go easy on him. Beat him senseless.

14
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:09,620
He's asking for it.

15
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:14,780
You're always teaching my wife how to bully me.

16
00:02:14,780 --> 00:02:17,480
When are you going to find someone
to keep you in line?

17
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,139
Me?

18
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:21,220
I'll leave it to fate.

19
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:24,000
If I meet the right person, I'll date.

20
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,000
If not, being like this is fine.

21
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,259
Isn't that right?

22
00:02:28,259 --> 00:02:30,020
Come on, eat up. This soup is excellent.

23
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:32,020
I've been stewing it all morning.
Hurry and eat.

24
00:02:32,020 --> 00:02:33,960
The vegetables are good too.

25
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:41,360
So, tell us.

26
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:44,020
What's going on with you and Miao Jing?

27
00:02:55,648 --> 00:02:57,508
Right now...

28
00:02:58,393 --> 00:02:59,995
I just don't know what she's thinking.

29
00:02:59,995 --> 00:03:02,841
That's simple. Let me teach you.

30
00:03:02,841 --> 00:03:06,020
When they say "no," they actually mean "yes."

31
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:09,539
When they say they're "not mad" anymore,
it means they're still "mad".

32
00:03:09,539 --> 00:03:11,430
Just assume the opposite of what they say.

33
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:12,660
Nonsense.

34
00:03:12,660 --> 00:03:14,060
Absolute nonsense.

35
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:15,979
How can you assume the opposite?

36
00:03:15,979 --> 00:03:17,860
Everything should be taken literally.

37
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:19,719
Are you married?

38
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:21,240
No.

39
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:26,260
Then, in this room,
who has the most successful experience?

40
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:27,620
The dog.

41
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:29,420
Silly dog.

42
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,680
Take this back.

43
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,440
Let them go.

44
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:36,680
Just eat your food.

45
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:42,338
Then...

46
00:03:42,338 --> 00:03:46,559
what if she says, "We'll see,"
and tells me to figure it out myself?

47
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:52,090
Well... that is a bit harder.

48
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:56,460
But I think
you need to analyze the specific situation.

49
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:59,740
Is it possible for you
to try a different approach?

50
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:03,639
For example,
try acting cute with her or something.

51
00:04:03,639 --> 00:04:05,820
- Get lost.
- Stop giving him bad advice.

52
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:07,767
You always use that method
to avoid the real issues.

53
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:09,740
You never admit your actual mistakes.

54
00:04:09,740 --> 00:04:12,460
That's why I was so angry before
that I wanted us to live apart.

55
00:04:22,565 --> 00:04:24,283
Yi.

56
00:04:24,283 --> 00:04:29,100
I think first, you need to find out
the real problem between the two of you.

57
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,500
Dating and building a life together
are two different things.

58
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,020
Dating is all about romance.

59
00:04:33,020 --> 00:04:36,000
If there's a little friction,
you can just let it slide.

60
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,200
You don't have to worry about the future.

61
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:40,459
But building a life together
is different after all.

62
00:04:40,459 --> 00:04:42,139
You can't just leave things vague.

63
00:04:42,139 --> 00:04:45,053
Exactly. You should listen to her. She's right.

64
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:48,380
Building a life together
is about mutual effort.

65
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:51,700
If one person is always giving,
and the other is always taking,

66
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:54,580
the relationship will eventually collapse.

67
00:04:57,513 --> 00:04:58,992
So...

68
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,940
What should I do specifically?

69
00:05:01,940 --> 00:05:04,140
I'm just speaking in general terms.

70
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:07,300
As for the specifics,
you'll have to figure it out, Yi.

71
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:12,660
Why don't you start with some simple things?

72
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:14,139
Call her tonight.

73
00:05:14,139 --> 00:05:16,760
Say things like, "I miss you",

74
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:18,279
"Are you tired?"

75
00:05:18,279 --> 00:05:20,620
or "You've been working hard."

76
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:23,279
What do you think?

77
00:05:23,279 --> 00:05:24,579
What are you laughing at?

78
00:05:24,579 --> 00:05:26,899
- Nothing.
- What she said was great.

79
00:05:26,899 --> 00:05:28,160
She's a master of love.

80
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,279
A toast to Qiao.

81
00:05:29,279 --> 00:05:30,699
- To her.
- To Qiao.

82
00:05:30,699 --> 00:05:32,680
Eat. Have some food.

83
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,379
- Are you praising me?
- Yes, we are.

84
00:05:34,379 --> 00:05:36,959
We really are. You're good.

85
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:53,820
<i>Start with some simple things.</i>

86
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,340
<i>Call her tonight.</i>

87
00:05:55,340 --> 00:05:57,960
<i>Say things like, "I miss you",</i>

88
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,460
<i>"Are you tired?"</i>

89
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:01,800
<i>or "You've been working hard."</i>

90
00:06:14,770 --> 00:06:15,820
<i>Hello?</i>

91
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:17,720
Are you off work?

92
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,380
What's wrong with your voice?

93
00:06:25,202 --> 00:06:28,340
Nothing. I just caught a bit of a cold.

94
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:34,600
Have you eaten?

95
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,380
I have dinner with a client later.

96
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:40,700
What about you?

97
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:44,140
<i>I ate at Bo's, but I didn't really eat my fill.</i>

98
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:47,579
In a bit, I'll head home.

99
00:06:47,579 --> 00:06:48,800
<i>What?</i>

100
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,360
You lost your appetite because I'm gone?

101
00:06:57,153 --> 00:06:59,213
What are you laughing at?

102
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,780
I miss you.

103
00:07:07,279 --> 00:07:08,979
Me too.

104
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:15,000
All right. Hearing you say that,
I suddenly have an appetite.

105
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,600
I'll eat more later.

106
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,540
You should eat something
to line your stomach, too.

107
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:19,740
Wait for me to come back.

108
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,200
Okay?

109
00:07:25,185 --> 00:07:26,705
I'm hanging up.

110
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:47,760
[Miao Jing's Coming Home]

111
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,329
Hello?

112
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:45,760
<i>Hello, Chen. It's Ma Yang.</i>

113
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,960
It's so late. What's the matter?

114
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:53,520
Yu and I are at the hospital now.

115
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:56,280
Jing's mother just fainted at the hotel.

116
00:09:58,380 --> 00:09:59,460
Which hospital?

117
00:09:59,460 --> 00:10:02,147
We're at the Teng City First People's Hospital.

118
00:10:02,147 --> 00:10:04,067
<i>I'll be right there.</i>

119
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:17,640
Hello, Yu. I reached Chen. He's on his way.

120
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,940
Yeah, I have to wait for him to fill this out.

121
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:21,139
He'll be here soon.

122
00:10:21,139 --> 00:10:22,956
Okay.

123
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:25,340
- Ma Yang.
- Chen.

124
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:27,220
- Where is she?
- She's still in the Resuscitation Room.

125
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:29,816
She isn't out yet. Xiao Yu is with her.

126
00:10:29,816 --> 00:10:31,720
How is she now? Why did she pass out like that?

127
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,560
I don't know either.

128
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:35,279
All I have is her identification card.

129
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:37,058
There is a lot I can't fill in.

130
00:10:37,058 --> 00:10:39,461
So we had to wait for you.

131
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,665
Sorry to trouble you both.

132
00:10:41,665 --> 00:10:42,680
No problem.

133
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,100
Have you reached Miao Jing?

134
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:46,220
I called, but Jing didn't answer.

135
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:48,220
She might be busy.

136
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,900
She's been completely swamped
these past two days.

137
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,159
Don't tell her yet.

138
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:53,759
I'm here to handle this.

139
00:10:53,759 --> 00:10:55,220
Okay.

140
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:59,200
Yu.

141
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,560
You're here.

142
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,340
How long has she been in there?

143
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:05,000
Over half an hour.
The doctor hasn't come out yet.

144
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,100
[Resuscitation Room]

145
00:11:37,460 --> 00:11:39,640
Wei Ming Zhen's family.

146
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:44,040
Doctor, how is she?

147
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:48,420
After emergency treatment,
she's out of immediate danger for now.

148
00:11:48,420 --> 00:11:50,100
But our tests show

149
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:53,320
that the cancer cells have spread
to her lungs and liver.

150
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:56,060
It's stage four breast cancer.

151
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,880
How could this happen?

152
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:01,900
How much time does she have?

153
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:06,280
That depends on her treatment plan
and how well her body recovers.

154
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:08,801
If she recovers well,
she can choose chemotherapy.

155
00:12:08,801 --> 00:12:12,080
If not, we can only offer palliative care.

156
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:16,960
And judging by her current condition,
I don't think this is news to her.

157
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,781
So you should be prepared.

158
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:21,113
Okay?

159
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:34,120
This is a big deal.
Shouldn't we discuss it with Jing?

160
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:36,240
I just don't know if she can get away.

161
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:38,180
I'll handle it.

162
00:12:38,180 --> 00:12:41,039
Thanks for everything today.
Go home and get some rest.

163
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:42,920
It's fine, Yi.

164
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:47,141
We'll get going, then.

165
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:49,440
We'll head out.

166
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,779
By the way.

167
00:12:50,779 --> 00:12:53,300
Please don't bring this up at the company.

168
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:54,493
Just act like you don't know.

169
00:12:54,493 --> 00:12:56,337
All right.

170
00:12:56,337 --> 00:12:58,294
We're off. Let's go.

171
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:22,320
The patient is still under anesthesia.
She should wake in about half an hour.

172
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:26,340
Her condition is critical,
so she must be watched at all times.

173
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:28,260
Don't leave her alone.

174
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:44,379
What about Jing?

175
00:13:44,379 --> 00:13:46,220
She's still away on business.

176
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:48,360
And now her mother suddenly...

177
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:51,330
Who could have expected something like this?

178
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,019
Good thing she has a brother.

179
00:13:53,019 --> 00:13:56,200
He may not be her real brother, but...

180
00:13:57,159 --> 00:14:02,500
Xiao Yu, do you think
Aunt Wei could be Chen's stepmother?

181
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,039
I don't know.

182
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:06,980
Jing rarely tells me about her family.

183
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:11,100
But she once told me that when she was little,
she came to Teng City with her mother.

184
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:14,660
If Chen Yi really is her brother,
then that pretty much settles it.

185
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:18,320
No wonder Chen told me not to talk about it.

186
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:21,060
That was pretty thoughtful of him.

187
00:14:23,580 --> 00:14:26,800
For a guy who's not even related to her,
he's gone above and beyond.

188
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:32,500
- Let's take a cab home. Let's go.
- Let's go.

189
00:14:57,140 --> 00:14:59,160
Miao Jing is away on business.

190
00:15:03,086 --> 00:15:04,926
Don't say anything yet.

191
00:15:05,580 --> 00:15:09,600
I need to ask you something.
If I'm right, just nod.

192
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:18,060
You came back to see Miao Jing this time
for money, right?

193
00:15:23,826 --> 00:15:25,753
You don't want money.

194
00:15:25,753 --> 00:15:28,393
Then you want Jing to support you in old age?

195
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,180
I called Miao Jing.

196
00:15:59,019 --> 00:16:01,199
She'll be back tonight.

197
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,800
Stay out of it.

198
00:16:07,580 --> 00:16:08,860
Don't worry.

199
00:16:08,860 --> 00:16:10,700
It's not that I want to get involved.

200
00:16:15,822 --> 00:16:17,168
[Teng City First People's Hospital]

201
00:16:17,168 --> 00:16:19,940
[Miao: I'll be there soon.]

202
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,861
How is she?

203
00:16:35,344 --> 00:16:37,413
The doctor said it's a breast issue.

204
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:41,233
As for the details, I'll go ask with you later.

205
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:43,721
Let's go.

206
00:16:57,620 --> 00:17:00,940
You should go home first.
I'll stay here tonight.

207
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,360
I'll stay with you.

208
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:05,620
Tomorrow, I'll find a caregiver.

209
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:07,760
That way, it'll be easier on you.

210
00:17:14,338 --> 00:17:15,899
Don't worry.

211
00:17:15,899 --> 00:17:17,539
I'm here.

212
00:18:59,859 --> 00:19:01,741
I'm fine.

213
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:06,520
I can be discharged in a few days.

214
00:19:09,378 --> 00:19:11,559
I'll find you a caregiver tomorrow.

215
00:19:11,559 --> 00:19:13,039
I have work during the day.

216
00:19:13,039 --> 00:19:14,284
No.

217
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:22,260
Either you do as I say, or I'm done helping.

218
00:19:46,061 --> 00:19:47,562
<i>Hey, Yi.</i>
[Inpatient Department]

219
00:19:47,562 --> 00:19:50,080
<i>You asked me to ask Fat Dragon
about Wei Ming Zhen.</i>

220
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,740
<i>They just texted me.</i>

221
00:19:51,740 --> 00:19:54,740
<i>They found out Wei Ming Zhen has remarried
in Peng City.</i>

222
00:19:54,740 --> 00:19:56,420
<i>She's a stepmother now.</i>

223
00:19:56,420 --> 00:19:59,480
<i>His family seems pretty well-off.</i>

224
00:20:03,340 --> 00:20:04,901
Come in.

225
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:08,980
Hello.

226
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:11,579
I'm a family member of Wei Ming Zhen,
the patient in bed 18.

227
00:20:11,579 --> 00:20:13,099
What is your relation to her?

228
00:20:13,099 --> 00:20:14,480
Her daughter.

229
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:17,340
Sounds like she's done all right
over the past few years.

230
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:19,441
Then why did she come back?

231
00:20:20,579 --> 00:20:22,460
<i>Not necessarily.</i>

232
00:20:22,460 --> 00:20:24,640
<i>The man has a son at home, too.</i>

233
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:26,700
He should be in middle school now.

234
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:29,019
My friend in Peng City sells insurance.

235
00:20:29,019 --> 00:20:31,420
<i>When he asked around,
he also found an inquiry form from Wei.</i>

236
00:20:31,420 --> 00:20:33,580
<i>It was about cancer coverage.</i>

237
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:36,660
<i>But that plan was expensive,
so she never followed through.</i>

238
00:20:36,660 --> 00:20:38,600
Late-stage cancer.

239
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,099
Wasn't she just here for observation
for a few days?

240
00:20:41,099 --> 00:20:43,960
Let me explain her condition first.

241
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:48,300
The patient has breast cancer, stage four.

242
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:50,300
In other words, it's late-stage.

243
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:56,140
The cancer has spread to her bones,
her skull, liver, and lungs,

244
00:20:56,140 --> 00:20:58,819
as well as her pleura and other areas.

245
00:20:58,819 --> 00:21:01,160
In other words, it's spread.

246
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:05,803
Her vital organs are already failing.

247
00:21:06,566 --> 00:21:08,087
At this stage,

248
00:21:08,087 --> 00:21:13,293
treatment is focused on
easing her pain and prolonging her life.

249
00:21:14,559 --> 00:21:16,260
This is her pathology report.

250
00:21:16,260 --> 00:21:18,120
You can take a look.

251
00:21:21,303 --> 00:21:25,284
The results show signs of prior drug therapy.

252
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:29,059
But in the past year, it looks like
she hasn't continued with that treatment.

253
00:21:29,059 --> 00:21:31,160
This caused the cancer cells to spread fast.

254
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,760
Then her condition got much worse.

255
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:38,020
<i>Later, I heard Wei Ming Zhen
spent a long time in the hospital.</i>

256
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:40,360
<i>The man couldn't support
both a patient and a student.</i>

257
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:42,640
<i>So they split up.</i>

258
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,080
Okay. I understand.

259
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,670
Get some rest.

260
00:21:56,579 --> 00:21:58,620
Things were critical this afternoon.

261
00:21:58,620 --> 00:22:01,460
At the time, she had
no immediate family there with her.

262
00:22:01,460 --> 00:22:05,240
So we followed emergency protocol
and tried to save her.

263
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:08,880
As her family, you have no objection, right?

264
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,440
Good.

265
00:22:11,579 --> 00:22:14,740
These are the informed consent form
and the surgery consent form.

266
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:17,200
They need to be signed by the next of kin.

267
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:29,100
[Miao Jing]

268
00:22:30,619 --> 00:22:34,040
How much time does she have left?

269
00:22:35,924 --> 00:22:37,796
It doesn't look good.

270
00:22:37,796 --> 00:22:42,460
Given her current condition, a month at most.

271
00:22:44,374 --> 00:22:46,000
Is there anything else we can do?

272
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,009
There are two options.

273
00:22:49,009 --> 00:22:51,590
One is chemotherapy alone.

274
00:22:51,590 --> 00:22:55,420
The other is chemotherapy with targeted drugs.

275
00:22:55,420 --> 00:23:00,220
But that option would be extremely expensive.

276
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:03,410
Honestly, given her current condition,

277
00:23:03,410 --> 00:23:06,400
both options may end up about the same.

278
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:10,620
As her family, you should prepare yourselves.

279
00:23:10,620 --> 00:23:15,640
As for the next treatment plan,
think it over and let me know, all right?

280
00:23:55,220 --> 00:23:58,720
[Convenience Store]

281
00:24:11,079 --> 00:24:12,860
One yuan.

282
00:24:52,099 --> 00:24:55,020
Don't pick up this habit.
It's bad for your lungs.

283
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:04,700
I put the blanket on her, and she's asleep.

284
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:07,440
I'll move her to a private room tomorrow.

285
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:10,200
Then I'll go home
and get her some clean clothes.

286
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:18,696
I'll hand off my work and take a few days off.

287
00:25:19,380 --> 00:25:21,480
I've thought it through.

288
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:23,500
I still want to go ahead with the treatment.

289
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:55,640
Okay.

290
00:25:57,380 --> 00:26:00,260
I'm not tired. Don't worry.

291
00:26:00,260 --> 00:26:03,040
Is the little one out of school yet?

292
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:05,140
Put the little one on the phone.

293
00:26:06,559 --> 00:26:08,460
Sweetie.

294
00:26:08,460 --> 00:26:11,400
Do you miss Grandma?

295
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:15,761
I miss you so much.

296
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:19,600
Your teacher praised you today?

297
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,720
You're such a star.

298
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:25,679
Later, I will bring you a pink doll.

299
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:28,599
Okay.

300
00:26:28,599 --> 00:26:30,099
Bye!

301
00:26:30,099 --> 00:26:32,080
See you later.

302
00:26:36,140 --> 00:26:37,859
No. Don't.

303
00:26:37,859 --> 00:26:40,480
Call me. If you need anything, call me.

304
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:43,259
I'll do it. Want some water? Here.

305
00:26:43,259 --> 00:26:44,980
Here.

306
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:47,080
Easy. Here.

307
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:58,960
Be careful.

308
00:27:01,100 --> 00:27:03,360
I mean, you're this sick.

309
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:06,140
Why hasn't your daughter come to see you?

310
00:27:07,420 --> 00:27:10,080
My daughter is at work.

311
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:14,700
They can't manage without her.

312
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:19,840
No matter how busy, when her mom is sick,
she should show up and take care of her mom.

313
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:21,960
What's the point of spending money
if she doesn't show she cares?

314
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:24,066
She'll be here soon.

315
00:27:27,180 --> 00:27:29,920
Besides, I'm fine.

316
00:27:35,259 --> 00:27:37,039
Your daughter is that busy with work.

317
00:27:37,039 --> 00:27:39,180
Is she dating anyone?

318
00:27:40,779 --> 00:27:42,480
If you ask me,

319
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:43,980
you may not be worried now,

320
00:27:43,980 --> 00:27:48,840
but when you see other grandparents
holding their grandkids,

321
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:51,060
you'll start to panic.

322
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:55,080
So noisy.

323
00:27:56,500 --> 00:27:58,480
The television's too loud, right?

324
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:00,420
I'll turn it off for you.

325
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:12,480
Eat a little.

326
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:13,980
Here.

327
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:18,280
Here.

328
00:28:18,980 --> 00:28:22,061
Good. You need to eat more.

329
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:28,120
Mei, you can head back. I'll stay with her.

330
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:33,820
Your mom barely ate. Try to feed her some more.

331
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:38,653
Call me if anything comes up.

332
00:28:38,653 --> 00:28:40,193
Okay.

333
00:28:54,940 --> 00:28:57,400
What are you doing here now?

334
00:28:58,940 --> 00:29:00,740
I asked for time off.

335
00:29:00,740 --> 00:29:03,480
I won't go in for the next couple of days.

336
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:08,080
Why take time off? Go back to work.

337
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,180
Making money matters.

338
00:29:12,660 --> 00:29:16,880
To you, money always comes first.

339
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:22,040
If a woman has no money, she has nothing.

340
00:30:20,019 --> 00:30:21,840
What is it?

341
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,900
Does it hurt?

342
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:34,680
Feeling better?

343
00:30:44,544 --> 00:30:46,064
Here.

344
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:53,520
Gently.

345
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:05,240
Lying down feels awful.

346
00:31:07,536 --> 00:31:10,477
I want to go walk around.

347
00:31:11,660 --> 00:31:14,000
Dr. Cui said you can't get out of bed.

348
00:31:38,140 --> 00:31:42,460
The doctor said
you can still get some air in a wheelchair.

349
00:32:27,099 --> 00:32:28,380
Mom.

350
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:30,400
Doctor, please save her!

351
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:33,740
Mom, please hang on.

352
00:32:33,740 --> 00:32:36,220
Nothing can happen to you!

353
00:32:39,700 --> 00:32:45,080
With a scene like this,
they must be fighting the Grim Reaper.

354
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:50,460
When I die, will you burn paper money for me?

355
00:32:53,060 --> 00:32:54,327
How much do you want?

356
00:32:54,327 --> 00:32:56,240
As much as possible.

357
00:32:57,160 --> 00:33:02,208
With paper money,
a lot of things get easier to handle.

358
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:23,220
I'm leaving this money to you.

359
00:33:23,220 --> 00:33:25,780
Use it to burn offerings for me.

360
00:33:26,460 --> 00:33:29,080
You don't need to burn much each year.

361
00:33:29,080 --> 00:33:31,580
Just remember to do it every year.

362
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:38,120
Go back and get some rest.

363
00:34:33,700 --> 00:34:36,840
[Inpatient Department]

364
00:35:13,199 --> 00:35:15,860
- Miao Jing.
- She's gone.

365
00:35:20,815 --> 00:35:22,780
Don't panic.
I'll have a nurse check the cameras.

366
00:35:22,780 --> 00:35:24,420
Let's look outside first.

367
00:35:31,659 --> 00:35:34,139
Hi. Have you seen the patient in Bed 18?

368
00:35:34,139 --> 00:35:36,620
- No.
- Okay, thank you.

369
00:36:26,420 --> 00:36:28,320
Let's go back.

370
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:44,280
I don't want to be...

371
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:48,720
a pathetic failure

372
00:36:49,580 --> 00:36:52,100
and an unclean woman.

373
00:36:55,790 --> 00:36:58,290
Even at the very last second,

374
00:37:02,473 --> 00:37:04,447
I still want

375
00:37:07,399 --> 00:37:09,740
to look beautiful.

376
00:37:09,740 --> 00:37:11,929
Don't be ridiculous.

377
00:37:12,659 --> 00:37:15,300
Even if I die,

378
00:37:22,099 --> 00:37:25,260
I don't want to die on that little bed.

379
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:30,520
Stinking and pathetic,

380
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:34,400
like a dirty old rag.

381
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,480
What is it?

382
00:37:53,660 --> 00:37:55,500
Jing.

383
00:37:59,180 --> 00:38:01,520
I promise you,

384
00:38:02,900 --> 00:38:04,900
from now on,

385
00:38:07,999 --> 00:38:13,146
I'll be... a better mom.

386
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:12,479
<i>You lazy bum.</i>

387
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:16,060
<i>Oh my God, hurry up.</i>

388
00:39:16,060 --> 00:39:17,400
<i>Does making a fire have to take this long?</i>

389
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:20,980
<i>I'm starving. Are you trying to starve me?</i>

390
00:39:20,980 --> 00:39:22,200
<i>You lazy bum.</i>

391
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:23,600
<i>What did you say?</i>

392
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:24,980
<i>Get out of here.</i>

393
00:39:24,980 --> 00:39:26,960
<i>Come here.</i>

394
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:28,300
<i>Is that how you talk to your cousin?</i>

395
00:39:28,300 --> 00:39:30,400
<i>Is that how you talk to your cousin?</i>

396
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,840
<i>- What are you doing?
- What do you mean, "what are you doing"?</i>

397
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:33,119
<i>- Why are you hitting my son?
- Didn't you hear how he spoke?</i>

398
00:39:33,119 --> 00:39:34,260
<i>- Move aside.
- Go inside and do your homework.</i>

399
00:39:34,260 --> 00:39:36,219
<i>Go. Every single day with this.</i>

400
00:39:36,219 --> 00:39:40,060
<i>Why isn't dinner ready yet? It's been ages.</i>

401
00:39:40,780 --> 00:39:43,960
<i>You just can't do anything right.</i>

402
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,960
<i>- Ming Zhen. Why are you here?
- Sister.</i>

403
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:52,840
<i>I came back to see you.</i>

404
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:55,640
<i>- Where's Jing?
- Jing? She's inside.</i>

405
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:57,420
<i>Has she been behaving lately?</i>

406
00:39:57,420 --> 00:40:00,300
<i>She's been very well-behaved.
You can rest easy with her here.</i>

407
00:40:00,300 --> 00:40:04,280
<i>Actually, I came this time to take Jing home.</i>

408
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:06,320
<i>Leaving her here has been
too much trouble for you.</i>

409
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:09,159
<i>- I feel so bad about it.
- It's fine, really.</i>

410
00:40:09,159 --> 00:40:12,280
<i>Right. I brought these
for you and your husband.</i>

411
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:14,000
<i>You don't have to bring anything.</i>

412
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:16,160
<i>I'll get you a glass of water.</i>

413
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:34,294
<i>Jing.</i>

414
00:40:34,294 --> 00:40:36,600
<i>I'm here to pick you up.</i>

415
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,940
<i>I'm taking you home.</i>

416
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:54,520
<i>Of course.
From now on, I'll be with you every day.</i>

417
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:57,020
<i>And I'll take you to the amusement park.</i>

418
00:40:57,020 --> 00:41:00,703
<i>We'll ride roller coasters, watch fireworks,
and eat big burgers. Okay?</i>

419
00:41:00,703 --> 00:41:02,599
<i>- Okay.
- Whatever you want to do in the future,</i>

420
00:41:02,599 --> 00:41:04,219
<i>I'll do it with you.</i>

421
00:41:04,219 --> 00:41:08,380
<i>Whatever other kids have,
I'll make sure you have it too.</i>

422
00:41:13,200 --> 00:41:14,660
<i>Here.</i>

423
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:05,620
The morgue charges by the day.
The family should arrange the funeral soon.

424
00:42:22,300 --> 00:42:24,500
Someone needs to handle the paperwork.

425
00:42:43,479 --> 00:42:45,479
I'll go handle the paperwork.

426
00:42:46,817 --> 00:42:48,577
Wait here for me.

427
00:43:07,647 --> 00:43:09,507
I'll be right back.

